snippet.textDisplay: Can I point out some extra changes you can make to avoid COVID-19 AND support local businesses? One, you brought home all those boxes and bowls, but you didn't clean the outsides or put on gloves to empty them. Then you touched your counter, pots, bowl, sink, etc. Two, was that 20 seconds of handwashing? Did you scrub your palms, "crank" your thumbs, and weave your fingers? Three, you touched your face at least 3-4 times, including an eye rub. Four, after washing your hands, you returned to the pot that you'd just handled before washing your hands, so you potentially contaminated your hands again. These are kind of anal-retentive, but I'd rather say it than just think it and not share. Stay safe and healthy, everyone!
